# ohpcc-nmbu skill — per-project config for the NMBU Orion HPC cluster.
#
# Copy this to `hpc.env` (or `.hpc/hpc.env`) at your PROJECT root and fill in.
# The wrappers walk up from the current directory to find it. Shell-sourceable
# (KEY=value, no spaces around `=`). No secrets here — safe to commit and share.

# --- cluster identity ---------------------------------------------------

# SSH alias for the LOGIN node (shell + sbatch), defined in ~/.ssh/config with
# ControlMaster/ControlPersist. See reference/ssh_setup.md.
HPC_HOST=orion

# SSH alias for the TRANSFER node (rsync/scp). On Orion the login node kills any
# command over 5 minutes, so all data transfers go through the file-transfer
# host (filemanager.orion.nmbu.no), which shares the same filesystems. Omit this
# line to reuse HPC_HOST (correct for single-host clusters).
HPC_TRANSFER_HOST=orion-filemanager

# Your NMBU/Orion username (used to filter `squeue`).
HPC_USER=your-nmbu-username

# SLURM account to charge. On Orion this is `nmbu` (the only account for now).
HPC_ACCOUNT=nmbu

# --- the write boundary -------------------------------------------------

# THE most important setting. Every remote write (push, submit, fetch) is
# refused unless it lands under this directory. Absolute path you own, no shell
# metacharacters (no $VARS — the guard rejects them). On Orion use project
# storage, /mnt/project/<group>/<you> (persistent, backed up, shared with your
# group). Alternative: /mnt/SCRATCH/<you> (bigger, faster to grow, but PURGED
# after 180 days — move anything you want to keep to /mnt/project).
HPC_REMOTE_ROOT=/mnt/project/<PROJECT>/your-subdir

# --- defaults (override per-job on the command line) --------------------

# Default SLURM partition. Orion batch partitions: `orion` (CPU, the default)
# and `GPU` (note: UPPERCASE — lowercase `gpu` is rejected by sbatch). Do NOT
# submit batch jobs to RStudio/JupyterLab/OOD/TestLab — those are Open OnDemand
# interactive partitions. For a GPU job set HPC_PARTITION=GPU AND pass `--gpus N`
# to hpc_submit.py (it requests 0 GPUs by default).
HPC_PARTITION=orion

# Email for SLURM notifications. Single jobs mail END,FAIL; array/chunked jobs
# are clamped to FAIL only (NMBU caps outbound email at ~200/day). Blank = off.
HPC_MAIL_USER=your.name@nmbu.no

# Subdirectory under HPC_REMOTE_ROOT holding pushed code; job working directory.
HPC_CODE_SUBDIR=repo

# What `hpc_push.sh` (no args) syncs up, space-separated, relative to the project
# root. Include your environment spec so it rides up with the code.
HPC_PUSH_PATHS="src scripts environment.yml"

# Shell lines injected into every job before your command. Use SINGLE quotes so
# $REMOTE_ROOT / $HOME expand inside the job, not when this file is read. The
# Orion-recommended micromamba pattern (create the env once on the login or
# transfer node first: `module load Miniforge3 && micromamba create -f
# environment.yml -n <env>`):
HPC_JOB_SETUP='module load Miniforge3; export MAMBA_ROOT_PREFIX=$HOME/.micromamba_root; eval "$(micromamba shell hook --shell bash)"; micromamba activate <env>'

# --- local bookkeeping --------------------------------------------------
# HPC_LOCAL_ROOT=.                       # defaults to the dir containing hpc.env
# HPC_AUDIT_LOG=.hpc_audit.log           # JSONL audit trail (gitignored)

# --- safety toggles (usually leave unset) -------------------------------
# HPC_PUSH_BACKUP=1                       # keep overwritten copies under .hpc_backups/<ts>
# HPC_ALLOW_UNOWNED_ROOT=1                # only for a genuinely shared root you don't own
